<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-5383] TJSONProtocol Java readString throws on bounds check </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-5383</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/blob/7e537505f014d8ede86f30a7500136c2f3e99505/lib/java/src/org/apache/thrift/protocol/TJSONProtocol.java#L976&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/blob/7e537505f014d8ede86f30a7500136c2f3e99505/lib/java/src/org/apache/thrift/protocol/TJSONProtocol.java#L976&lt;/a&gt;&#160;this line appears to be unnecessary. The following code works with thrift 0.13.0 and fails with an exception on 0.14.x&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; TMemoryBuffer buf = new TMemoryBuffer(11); TMemoryBuffer buf = new TMemoryBuffer(11); &lt;br/&gt;
TJSONProtocol prot = new TJSONProtocol(buf); &lt;br/&gt;
prot.writeString(&quot;yeehaw&quot;); &lt;br/&gt;
prot.readString();&lt;/p&gt;</description>
